.help asivector Jul84 "Image Interpolator Package"
.ih
NAME
asivector -- evaluate the interpolant
.ih
SYNOPSIS
asivector (asi, x, y, npix)

.nf
    pointer	asi	# interpolator descriptor
    real	x[npix]	# x array, 1 <= x[i] <= npix
    real	y[npix]	# array of interpolated values
    int		npix	# number of x values
.fi
.ih
ARGUMENTS
.ls asi  
Pointer to the sequential interpolator descriptor structure.
.le
.ls x   
Array of x values.
.le
.ls y
Array of interpolated values.
.le
.ls npix   
The number of x values.
.le
.ih
DESCRIPTION
The polynomial coefficients are calculated directly from the data points. The
actual computation is done by adding and multiplying terms
according to Everett's central difference formula.
The spline interpolant uses the B-spline
coefficients calculated by the ASIFIT routine.

The sinc interpolation is computed using a range of data points around
the desired position.
.ih
NOTES
Checking for out of bounds and INDEF valued pixels is the
responsibility of the user. ASIINIT and ASIFIT must be called before using
ASIVECTOR.
.ih
SEE ALSO
asieval, arieval
.endhelp
